race.description: The Jansz Tasmania Midway Maiden Plate
race.comment: RATIFY (4) started at 100/1 but caught the eye in the closing stages on debut last start over this distance at Warwick Farm, finishing fourth after making up about five lengths in the run home. Drops 1kg after the claim in an easier maiden. Ideally placed to break through. DASHING DOUBLE (1) settled back in the field and made no impression last time out over 1500m at Newcastle. Best figures measure up so off a 33-day freshen up he is worth another chance. LIGHTNESS (7) has not raced since failing on debut over 1250m at Canterbury in June. Trialled well at Hawkesbury recently and in this modest affair is capable of featuring. LUMA LIGHT (8) enjoyed the new role of leader least start when runner-up at Canberra. May prove hard to catch under a light weight if the same tactics are employed. SACHI (10) was just fair first-up at Nowra but she can improve over an extra furlong today.
